Project Title:
AI-Based Student Performance Prediction System

Problem Statement:
Many students struggle to track their academic performance and identify areas of improvement early. There is a need for a system that can analyze student data and predict future performance so that timely actions can be taken.

Objective:
To build a machine learning model that predicts student performance based on study habits and academic data.

Dataset:
The dataset will include:

Study hours
Attendance percentage
Internal marks
Previous semester scores
Assignment completion rate

Data can be collected manually or from publicly available student datasets.

Algorithm Used:
Linear Regression for predicting continuous marks
Decision Tree for classification of performance (Pass/Fail or Grades)

Methodology:
Collect and preprocess dataset
Handle missing values and normalize data
Train machine learning models
Evaluate model accuracy
Use model to predict student performance

Expected Output:
Predicted marks or grade of a student
Identification of weak areas
Suggestions for improvement based on input data

Tools & Technologies:
Python
Pandas, NumPy
Scikit-learn
Matplotlib
Conclusion:

This system will help students and educators make better decisions by providing early insights into academic performance and enabling timely interventions.
